[b]Wolfe Wave Scanner Pro[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Searches a depth window of confirmed swings for the best-scoring 5-point Wolfe Wave wedge — a contracting, alternating channel where point 5 tests the 1-3 trendline. Each candidate is scored 0-100 across seven structural criteria; the winning pattern draws the wedge, the internal zigzag, and an EPA (Estimated Price at Arrival) target projected from the true wedge apex, then stays tracked until price confirms or invalidates it.

[b]Scoring[/b]
[list]
[*]Wedge structure (point 3 undercuts/exceeds point 1, point 5 extends beyond point 3, point 4 stays contained between points 1 and 2)
[*]Channel contraction + boundary slope consistency
[*]Apex convergence of lines 1-3 and 2-4 ahead of point 5
[*]Point-5 trendline test against the 1-3 line
[*]Reward direction of the EPA target from point 5, capped to a sane distance
[*]Timing and leg-time symmetry of the five legs
[/list]

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Best-of-window swing search — not just the literal last 5 swings
[*]EPA target line from the correct 1-3/2-4 apex
[*]Live invalidation tracking with dedicated alert once a fired pattern breaks
[*]Near-miss candidate marker and score-breakdown debug table for threshold tuning
[*]Dashboard with status, best score, bias, EPA and invalidation level
[*]Bull/bear alerts with bar-close confirmation
[/list]

